<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 16:21:57 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>增强量子振荡工具箱</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/enhancing-the-quantum-oscillation-toolbox</link><description>一项新实验探讨了非线性霍尔响应中涉及的电子波函数的量子几何。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/enhancing-the-quantum-oscillation-toolbox2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 16:21:54 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/enhancing-the-quantum-oscillation-toolbox</guid></item><item><title>通过半导体界面工程双向操纵无门量子电子态</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/bidirectional-manipulation-of-gate-free-quantum-electronic-states-via-semiconductor-interface-engineering</link><description>最近的一项研究&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/bidirectional-manipulation-of-gate-free-quantum-electronic-states-via-semiconductor-interface-engineering.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 16:06:54 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/bidirectional-manipulation-of-gate-free-quantum-electronic-states-via-semiconductor-interface-engineering</guid></item><item><title>抽象代数解锁了量子系统的可区分状态</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/abstract-algebra-unlocks-distinguishable-states-for-quantum-systems</link><description>世界各地的研究人员正在竞相开发用于传感、通信、计算和控制的新型量子系统，这些系统有望超越传统系统。创建稳定、可测量、可区分的量子态（这将是任何此类系统的核心）是一项艰巨的任务。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/abstract-algebra-unlocks-distinguishable-states-for-quantum-systems3.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 15:51:54 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/abstract-algebra-unlocks-distinguishable-states-for-quantum-systems</guid></item><item><title>细菌揭示了将抗生素抗性外膜固定到细胞壁上的“胶水”蛋白</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/bacteria-reveal-glue-protein-that-fastens-antibiotic-resistant-outer-membrane-to-cell-wall</link><description>圣母大学的研究人员和合作者发现了革兰氏阴性细菌外膜如何附着在细胞壁上的一个关键过程，加深了对这些细菌如何频繁产生抗生素耐药性的理解。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/bacteria-reveal-glue-protein-that-fastens-antibiotic-resistant-outer-membrane-to-cell-wall.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 15:36:54 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/bacteria-reveal-glue-protein-that-fastens-antibiotic-resistant-outer-membrane-to-cell-wall</guid></item><item><title>脑机接口为 ALS 患者提供独立、准确的沟通</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/brain-computer-interface-enables-independent-accurate-communication-for-man-living-with-als</link><description>一项新研究表明，因肌萎缩侧索硬化症 (ALS) 导致严重瘫痪的人可以在家中使用脑机接口 (BCI) 与数字世界进行交流、工作和互动，而无需研究人员的支持。发表于&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/brain-computer-interface-enables-independent-accurate-communication-for-man-living-with-als2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 15:21:54 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/brain-computer-interface-enables-independent-accurate-communication-for-man-living-with-als</guid></item><item><title>半导体芯片液体冷却技术效率比之前记录高 10 倍</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/liquid-cooling-technology-for-semiconductor-chips-is-10-times-more-efficient-than-previous-record</link><description>人工智能数据中心非常耗电。人工智能计算不仅消耗大量电力，而且还需要大量能量来冷却运行过程中发热的半导体芯片。随着人工智能芯片不断提供更高的性能，它们产生的热量迅速增加。因此，传统的空气冷却和外部铜散热器已接近其实际极限。为了应对这一挑战，韩国科学技术院的研究团队开发了一种超高效液体冷却技术，可以从内部冷却半导体芯片。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/liquid-cooling-technology-for-semiconductor-chips-is-10-times-more-efficient-than-previous-record3.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 15:06:54 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/liquid-cooling-technology-for-semiconductor-chips-is-10-times-more-efficient-than-previous-record</guid></item><item><title>被动量子纠错使量子位寿命加倍，达到收支平衡点</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/passive-quantum-error-correction-doubles-qubit-lifetime-reaching-break-even-point</link><description>美国研究人员团队设计了一种被动量子纠错技术，使量子位能够纠正自己的错误。马萨诸塞大学阿默斯特分校的 Shruti Shirol 及其同事证明，该协议将量子位系统中不可避免的能量耗散从障碍转变为优势，为实验室外的实用量子计算提供了一条有希望的途径。该研究发表于&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/passive-quantum-error-correction-doubles-qubit-lifetime-reaching-break-even-point.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 14:51:54 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/passive-quantum-error-correction-doubles-qubit-lifetime-reaching-break-even-point</guid></item><item><title>临床医生和科学家发现与最致命的儿童脑癌有关的大脑网络</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/clinician-scientists-identify-brain-network-linked-to-deadliest-childhood-brain-cancer</link><description>伦敦大学学院的临床医生科学家们已经确定了与弥漫性中线神经胶质瘤（DMG）（最致命的儿童脑癌）儿童的生存相关的人类大脑网络，这提高了全新治疗方法的可能性。研究人员发现，DMG 肿瘤似乎利用大脑现有的神经回路来驱动肿瘤的生长和进展。与该网络联系更紧密的肿瘤与患者生存期显着缩短相关。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/clinician-scientists-identify-brain-network-linked-to-deadliest-childhood-brain-cancer.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 14:36:54 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/clinician-scientists-identify-brain-network-linked-to-deadliest-childhood-brain-cancer</guid></item><item><title>除了冷冻快照之外，结合成像方法还可以看到蛋白质的“呼吸”</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/beyond-frozen-snapshots-protein-breathing-comes-into-view-with-combined-imaging-methods</link><description>结构生物学的进步使科学家能够确定原子级细节的分子结构，有时会产生不能反映蛋白质动态的静态快照。然而，这些运动通常对于生物功能至关重要。奥地利科学技术研究所 (ISTA) 的研究人员与国际合作者合作，现已结合多种方法来阐明蛋白质如何“呼吸”以及一些实验技术如何冻结其运动。这些发现可以促进蛋白质设计方法并改进基于人工智能的结构预测工具&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/beyond-frozen-snapshots-protein-breathing-comes-into-view-with-combined-imaging-methods2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 14:21:54 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/beyond-frozen-snapshots-protein-breathing-comes-into-view-with-combined-imaging-methods</guid></item><item><title>准一维材料解锁了超出标准限制的电荷波电控制</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/quasi-1d-material-unlocks-electric-control-of-charge-waves-beyond-standard-limits</link><description>控制带负电粒子（即电子）运动的能力是所有现代电子设备功能的核心。这种控制通常是使用栅极（一种电极）来实现的，所施加的电场通过该电极改变材料的电特性。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/quasi-1d-material-unlocks-electric-control-of-charge-waves-beyond-standard-limits.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 14:06:54 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/quasi-1d-material-unlocks-electric-control-of-charge-waves-beyond-standard-limits</guid></item></channel></rss>